The '''Dolores-Guayaquil Megashear''' ({{lang-es|Megafalla Dolores-Guayaquil }}) is a first-order [[shear zone]] and [[fault zone]] in Northern South America.<ref name=Lavenu2006>{{Citation
| last  = Lavenu
| first = A.
| title = Andean neotectonics between 1°N and 47°S (Ecuador, Bolivia and Chile): A review
| journal = [[Revista de la Asociación Geológica Argentina]] 
| volume  = 61
| issue   = 4
| year    = 2006
| pages   = 504–524
| url     = http://www.scielo.org.ar/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&pid=S0004-48222006000400006
}}</ref> The megashear runs from the [[Gulf of Guayaquil]] in southwestern [[Ecuador]], through [[Colombia]], to [[Dolores, Venezuela|Dolores]] in [[Venezuela]].

