The following is a [[:Category:City timelines|timeline]] of the [[Goma#History|history]] of the [[List of cities in the Democratic Republic of the Congo|city]] of [[Goma]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. {{Dynamic list}} {{TOC right}}
==20th century== {{History of the Democratic Republic of the Congo}}
* 1925 - [[Virunga National Park|Albert National Park]] established near Goma. * 1959 - [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Goma]] founded.<ref>{{cite web |work=Chronology of Catholic Dioceses |title= Democratic Republic of the Congo |url= http://www.katolsk.no/organisasjon/verden/chronology/congo_kinshasa |publisher=[[Roman Catholic Diocese of Oslo]] |location=Norway |accessdate= 19 October 2017 }}</ref> * 1962 - Benezeth Moley becomes governor.<sup>([[:fr:Liste des gouverneurs du Nord-Kivu|fr]])</sup> * 1984 - Population: 77,908.<ref name=Brinkhoff /> * 1988 - Goma becomes part of newly formed [[North Kivu]] province.{{cn|date=October 2017}} * 1993 - [[University of Goma]] established. * 1994 ** Population: 161,956.<ref name=Kisangani2016 /> ** July: 850,000 [[Rwandan genocide|Rwandan war]] refugees flee to Goma.<ref name=Kisangani2016 /><ref name=Europa2001>{{cite book|publisher=[[Europa Publications]] |title=Political Chronology of Africa |series=Political Chronologies of the World |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=0O86sZdHfHUC |isbn=0203409957 |year= 2001 |chapter= Democratic Republic of the Congo |pages= 100-113 }}</ref> * 1996 - 2 November: Goma taken by [[Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo]].<ref name=Europa2001 /> * 1998 - 2 August: City taken by forces of [[Rally for Congolese Democracy–Goma]].<ref name=Kisangani2016>{{cite book|author=Emizet Francois Kisangani |title=Historical Dictionary of the Democratic Republic of the Congo |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sj9mDQAAQBAJ |edition=4th |year= 2016 |publisher=[[Rowman & Littlefield ]] |isbn= 9781442273160 }}</ref> * 2000 ** Yole!Africa cultural centre established.{{sfn|Gesthuizen|2013}}[https://yoleafrica.org] ** [[Eugène Serufuli Ngayabaseka]] becomes governor of North Kivu province.<sup>([[:fr:Liste des gouverneurs du Nord-Kivu|fr]])</sup>
==21st century== * 2002 - January: [[Mount Nyiragongo]] erupts, destroys nearly half of city structures.<ref name=bbc-timeline>{{cite web |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-13286306 |title=Democratic Republic of Congo Profile: Timeline |publisher=BBC News |accessdate= 19 October 2017 }}</ref> * 2004 - Population: 249,862 (estimate).<ref name=Brinkhoff>{{cite web |url=http://www.citypopulation.de/CongoDemRep-Cities_d.html |work= Citypopulation.de |title=Kongo (Dem. Rep.): Städte |language=de |publisher=Thomas Brinkhoff |location=Oldenburg, Germany |accessdate= 20 October 2017 }}</ref> * 2006 ** {{illm|Institut supérieur de statistique et de nouvelles technologies de Goma|fr}} (school) founded. ** Salaam Kivu International Film Festival begins.{{sfn|Gesthuizen|2013}}[https://yoleafrica.org/ciff/] * 2007 ** "New military operations centre for the [[FARDC]]" established.<ref>{{cite book|editor=Andreas Mehler |display-editors=etal |volume=4 |publisher=Koninklijke Brill |issn=1871-2525 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=aVGwKj6ER9kC |title=Africa Yearbook: Politics, Economy and Society South of the Sahara in 2007 |year= 2008 |chapter= Democratic Republic of the Congo |author= Denis M. Tull |pages= 239-254 }}</ref> ** [[Julien Paluku Kahongya]] becomes governor of North Kivu province. * 2008 ** January: International peace conference held in Goma.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.jeuneafrique.com/pays/rd-congo/chronologie |title= RD Congo: Chronologie |language=fr |work=[[Jeuneafrique.com]] |location=Paris |accessdate= 20 October 2017 }}</ref> ** 15 April: [[Hewa Bora Airways Flight 122|Airplane crash]] occurs. ** October: "Chaos grips...Goma as [[2008 Nord-Kivu campaign|rebel forces advance]]."<ref name=bbc-timeline /> * 2009 ** August: US secretary of state [[List_of_international_trips_made_by_the_United_States_Secretary_of_State#Hillary_Rodham_Clinton|visits]] Goma.<ref name=bbc-timeline /> ** Roger Rachid Tumbala becomes mayor (approximate date).[https://www.radiookapi.net/regions/nord-kivu/2010/12/13/poursuite-de-l%25e2%2580%2599operation-%25e2%2580%25b9-destruction-des-constructions-anarchiques%25e2%2580%25ba]{{timefact|date=October 2017}} * 2011 - Jean Busanga Malihaseme appointed mayor.<ref>{{citation |title=Adolphe Lumanu Nomme Un Nouveau Maire À La Tête La Ville De Goma Au Nord-Kivu |language=fr |url= http://www.lecongolais.cd/adolphe-lumanu-nomme-un-nouveau-maire-a-la-tete-la-ville-de-goma-au-nord-kivu/ |date= 30 September 2011 |work={{illm|Lecongolais.cd|no|LeCongolais}} }}</ref> * 2012 ** July: {{illm|Battle of Goma (2012)|fr|Bataille de Goma (2012)}} begins. ** 20 November: [[M23 rebellion|M23]] forces take Goma.<ref name=bbc-timeline /> ** 12 December: Prison break.<ref name=Kisangani2016 /> ** Kubuya Ndoole Naso becomes mayor.<ref>{{citation |url= https://www.radiookapi.net/actualite/2013/01/27/rdc-le-maire-de-goma-accuse-le-m23-de-causer-linsecurite-dans-la-peripherie-de-sa-ville/ |language=fr |title=RDC : le maire de Goma accuse le M23 de causer l’insécurité dans la périphérie de sa ville |date= 27 January 2013 |work=[[Radiookapi.net]] |location=DR Congo }}</ref> * 2013 ** 4 March: [[2013 Goma Compagnie Africaine d'Aviation Fokker 50 crash|Airplane crash]] occurs. ** August: Heavy fighting occurs outside Goma during the [[M23 rebellion]]. * 2015 ** January: [[2015 Congolese protests]]. ** June: Airport taken by "Mai-Mai fighters."<ref>{{citation |title=Gunmen attack airport in eastern Congo, seven dead |date=2 June 2015 |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-congodemocratic-fighting-idUSKBN0OI0U920150602 |publisher=Reuters }}</ref> ** Dieudonné Malere becomes mayor.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.radiookapi.net/2015/08/30/actualite/en-bref/dieudonne-malere-nomme-maire-de-goma |language=fr |title=Dieudonné Malere nommé maire de Goma |date=30 August 2015 |work=Radiookapi.net }}</ref> ** Population: 368,165 (estimate).<ref name=Kisangani2016 /> * 2016 - November: United Nations forces attacked by bomb.<ref>{{citation |title=Bomb attack kills child, wounds 32 Indian peacekeepers in east Congo: U.N. |date= 8 November 2016 |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-congo-un-idUSKBN1330NV |publisher=Reuters }}</ref>
